USE IN ANY ROOM – This shoe rack is an excellent option to keep any room of the home neat and clutter free. Use it in your entryway, garage, bedroom, or bathroom. The slatted design of the shoes rack offers ventilation and drainage for your footwear.

EASY ASSEMBLY – With no tools required, the shoe rack for closet floor is quick and easy to put together, no fuss. Simply fasten the rails to the side rails of the shoe organizer cubby and you are done.

Easy Tool-Free Assembly STEP 1 Connect four (4)40.7’’Lrods (C) to shelf end connector (A) on each end to make a shelf. reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Looks great for the price!
reviews.reviewText: Super easy to assemble. The color is so unique and looks a lot better than usual black racks. The common problem when I assemble racks made of metal bars and plastic joints is that the plastic parts are often very fragile and break easily when I insert the poles. But this one is made with good quality. I bought two of these racks, and no parts broke during the assembling process. Great choice to make use of space at the bottom of the closet!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on June 11, 2018
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Basic and Easy to Assemble
reviews.reviewText: Item arrived as described and I love it!This arrived in pieces ready to assemble. Parts were in individual bags by size so it was easy to make sure I had all parts before beginning assembly.Instructions were clear and easy to follow. No tools necessary and it took less than 10 minutes!The finished product is sturdy and holds about 10 pairs of shoes. It fits nicely in our entryway closet.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 11, 2020
reviews.reviewTitle: 3.0 out of 5 stars Easy to assemble. Cheap materials/flimsy
reviews.reviewText: This rack was easy to assemble. Everything was labeled, and it came with clear instructions. I would also recommend assembling with a rubber mallet to make sure that the bars stay secure. However, it's very flimsy, and the bars kept falling out while I was trying to put shoes on it. For the price it's okay, but it definitely wasn't designed for heavy use. I think that if I wasn't using this in my closet for shoe storage, it would absolutely break on me in a couple of months. That being said, it works for my needs, and the bars stopped falling once I hammered the ends a little more.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 3, 2019
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Perfect for my needs
reviews.reviewText: I wanted a long but not super high shoe rack to corral my husband's shoes. This fit the bill at a good price. It was super easy to assemble even though there were no directions in the box. Following another reviewer's suggestion, I placed it with the "handles" down so I could fit his flip flops and sandals underneath it on the floor, thus giving me three levels of shoe storage. I put it up against a wall which stabilized it. It fits 4 pairs plus one single shoe on each level. I would definitely buy another of these.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 27, 2023
reviews.reviewText: The box that this product was delivered in says “Home Complete.” This is not true. I open up the package to get ready for assemble . It has no instructions in the box. You have scroll down to where this product was advertised in Amazon to get information. I get it everything going digital. Also, they are missing parts. It not complete. The top handle part that curve and attaches to the top of shoe rack is missing. The delivery and box it came in was good. The chief complaint here are the missing parts. The product itself is made of cheap materials and of low quality. The price for this product is not worth it. The only reason I will be keeping it, is due to dimensions of the product and it will fit into the space I will be using it in.

We wanted shoe racks that would not slip heeless shoes off them because they were built with a downward slant. These flat shoe racks work well for running and casual shoes as well as shoes with heels.
I like it. It takes all my shoes.
